  "prompt": "What are some ways to put underline and Bold text in Facebook Chat? As previously we can do this by putting text in between underscore(_) and asterisk(*) for underline and bold text respectively?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, Facebook Messenger does not support the use of formatting like underscores (_) for underlining or asterisks (*) for bold text in chat. The formatting options that were once available for emphasizing text, such as those you mentioned, have been phased out.\n\nCurrently, Facebook Messenger primarily supports plain text for chat messages, and there are no built-in formatting features available for bold, italics, or underline. If you want to emphasize text, you may need to use alternative methods such as:\n\n1. **Using emojis or symbols:** You can use emojis or symbols to highlight or draw attention to specific messages.\n2. **All caps:** For emphasizing a word or phrase, you could use uppercase letters, but be mindful that using all caps can come across as shouting.\n3. **Sending separate messages:** If you want to emphasize something, you might consider breaking up your messages creatively or using a different message for emphasis.\n\nIf you are looking for updated formatting options, always check the latest version of the Messenger app or Facebook's help resources, as they may introduce new features over time.",
